  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is legally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by concealing its true origin. Specific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illicit funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic channels\n\nTypical legal elements include:\n- Knowingly disguising proceeds from criminal activity\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide illegal origins\n- Attempting to make unlawful funds appear legitimate\n- Transferring money to avoid reporting requirements\n\nSpecific definitions and penalties differ between countries, but most follow similar core principles established by international anti-money laundering (AML) standards.\n\nWould you like me to provide more detailed information about legal perspectives on money laundering?",
